OL,3,CWarning after batteries cause large
OL,4,Cbin lorry fire in Dorset
OL,6,F"Crushed batteries can cause fires,
OL,7,Fespecially when surrounded by highly
OL,8,Fflammable material like paper,
OL,9,Fcardboard, and plastic."
OL,11,FThe council urged people to dispose of
OL,12,Fbatteries in one of two ways.
OL,14,F"Batteries and battery-powered items
OL,15,Fcan be taken to any of our household
OL,16,Frecycling centres.
OL,18,F"Household batteries can be placed in
OL,19,Fa battery bag (or a clear sealable
OL,20,Fplastic bag) and left on top of your
OL,21,Frecycling bin for collection."
